<dl id="n12136g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12136g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12136g"> 136(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <u>Aryan</u></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> To resume then, in a few words, what is known about the ethnographical distribution of cases of &lsquo;Mongolian&rsquo; imbecility, it may be said that such are not seen amongst the Blacks, and are not known to occur amongst the <mark>Aryan</mark> populations of Asia, or even amongst the Arabs and pure Jews. <small> F.G. Crookshank, <a name="MIOM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MIOM"><cite title="source">The Mongol in Our Midst</cite></a> (1924) 126</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
